Under what three conditions will a vendor record be made inactive?,"- A vendor record is made inactive when the vendor name is auto-populated from the government database Enterprise Datahub (EDH) and is not editable.
- The record becomes inactive if the UEN Registered Company/Organisation name is auto-populated from the government database- Enterprise Datahub (EDH) and hence will not be allowed for edit.
- If, for any reason, the connection to the government database fails, the vendor name field will be unavailable for updating, and the record can be made inactive until connectivity is restored. [Source: Document Create_Update_Vendor_Record.pdf, Page 22]","[{'image': <PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=720x540 at 0x21FED3A9820>, 'source': 'Document Create_Update_Vendor_Record.pdf, page 22'}, {'image': <PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=595x842 at 0x21FEF67F950>, 'source': 'Document government-personal-data-protection-policies-jul21.pdf, page 27'}, {'image': <PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=595x842 at 0x21F9A880D70>, 'source': 'Document Guide to Data Protection Practices for ICT Systems.pdf, page 32'}, {'image': <PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=595x842 at 0x21F9A87EDB0>, 'source': 'Document supplier_guide_detailed.pdf, page 24'}, {'image': <PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=595x842 at 0x220352A4FB0>, 'source': 'Document WHO World health statistics 2025.pdf, page 8'}]"
